        output='# Segment Reporting Footnote Analysis\n\n## How the CODM Evaluates Segments\n\nThe footnote states that following the Mergers, the Company determined that effective Q1 2026, the Chief Executive Officer, acting as the CODM, **organizes the Company, manages resource allocations, and measures performance** among three operating and reportable segments: **(i) Space, (ii) Connectivity, and (iii) AI**.\n\nThe CODM specifically:\n- **Assesses performance and allocates resources based on segment income (loss) from operations**\n- **Compares actual income (loss) from operations to historical results and previously forecasted financial information**\n- The footnote begins to state "The Company\'s CODM does not evaluate operating and reportable segments using..." but the text is truncated, suggesting the CODM does *not* use some other measure (likely a non-GAAP measure or a different metric) for segment evaluation\n\nPrior period presentations were conformed to the current three-segment structure.\n\n## What Is Included in Segment Income (Loss) from Operations\n\nBased on the segment data tables, segment income (loss) from operations is calculated as **Revenue minus Total costs and expenses**, where Total costs and expenses includes:\n\n| Line Item | Included in Segment Measure |\n|---|---|\n| Revenue | ✅ Yes |\n| Cost of revenue | ✅ Yes |\n| Research and development | ✅ Yes |\n| Selling, general, and administrative | ✅ Yes |\n| Restructuring charges | ✅ Yes |\n| Impairment | ✅ Yes |\n\nFor 2025, this produced segment results of:\n- **Space:** $(657) million loss\n- **Connectivity:** $4,423 million income\n- **AI:** $(6,355) million loss\n- **Total Reportable Segments:** $(2,589) million loss\n\n## What Is Excluded from Segment Income (Loss) from Operations\n\nThe following items appear **only at the Total Reportable Segments / consolidated level** and are **not allocated to individual segments**:\n\n| Line Item | Allocated to Segments? |\n|---|---|\n| Interest