) rather than being corporate-level unallocated costs.\n\n4. **Non-GAAP Segment Adjusted EBITDA:** The footnote also reconciles segment income (loss) from operations to **Segment Adjusted EBITDA**, which excludes depreciation and amortization, share-based compensation, restructuring charges, and impairment from the segment measure. This is presented as a non-GAAP performance measure used by management, but the footnote clarifies that the **CODM\'s primary segment performance measure is segment income (loss) from operations** (the GAAP-based measure), not Segment Adjusted EBITDA.\n\n## Summary\n\n| Question | Answer |\n|---|---|\n| CODM evaluation metric | Segment income (loss) from operations, compared to historical results and forecasts |\n| Included in segment measure | Revenue, COGS, R&D, SG&A, restructuring charges, impairment |\n| Excluded from segment measure | Interest expense, interest income, other income (expense) net, income taxes |\n| Explicit shared cost / corporate allocation disclosures | **None explicitly disclosed** — no corporate segment, no unallocated column, no described allocation methodology |\n| Implicit unallocated items | Financing and non-operating items (interest, other income/expense) are not allocated to segments |',
